009_Nexus}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af7
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
In this video, I present the changes made to the Nexus.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
Instead of the Mothership, the Warp Prism can now be built directly at the Nexus, provided that a Cybernetics Core has been constructed. The Warp Prism can not only transport units and provide Psionic Matrix while in Phasing Mode, but it can also }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\loch
recharge shields}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 in Phasing Mode, similar to the former Shield Battery. As a result, the Shield Battery has been removed from the game. In addition, the Psionic Matrix}{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\loch
 radius}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 of the Warp Prism has been increased and now matches that of a Pylon, allowing Protoss structures to be powered more safely without having to place them too close to enemy attack range. In addition, the earlier availability of the Warp Prism is necessary to ensure that all races have equally fast options to leave or access islands. This change is very important to make much more diverse maps possible.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
Let\u8217\'92s move on to Strategic Recall. Previously, Protoss armies often had to be teleported back to the Nexus, because Protoss units had few retreat options, and armies could only be moved between bases slowly. Without Strategic Recall this often led to critical damage before reinforcements arrived and made comebacks difficult to achieve. However, since all units and structures now have more health and shields, most units deal less damage on average, and all races have received new or improved defensive tools, the early defensive option of }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\loch
Strategic Recall}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 is no longer required. Strategic Recall also feels very unfair for opponents, as even well-executed surrounds can be countered so easily.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
Furthermore, many Protoss units now have }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\loch
enhanced retreat capabilities}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
. These include earlier access to Warp Prisms with the }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\loch
Recharge Shields}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 ability, }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\loch
Zealot\u8217\'92s Charge}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
which can also be used for retreating, the }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\loch
double Blink}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 for Stalkers, and }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\loch
Adept Shades}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 that can instantly teleport to their shade via a button with a reduced cooldown, along with many other improvements. This means Protoss have more options to escape dangerous situations, but those options depend more on player skill. In addition, Protoss base defense has become significantly stronger overall, giving players far more time to reposition their armies for defense. These improved defensive options will be explored in greater detail in the upcoming videos.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
Therefore, }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\loch
Strategic Recall}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 has been removed from the Nexus and will return in a }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\loch
reworked form}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 with the Mothership\u8217\'92s replacement, the }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\loch
Arbiter, which can be built multiple times}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
Additionally, Nexuses no longer share the cooldown of the }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\loch
Energy Recharge}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 ability. Each Nexus can now use its own Recharge independently, restoring }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\loch
75 energy for 75 energy}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
. This change was made to allow players to recharge more units without excessive clicking. Each use provides enough energy for most abilities. While the ability itself is weaker due to the increased energy cost per point restored, it remains quite powerful thanks to the removed cooldown.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
With these changes, the Nexus now provides an important defensive unit as well as abilities, all of which can also be useful offensively in one way or another.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af7\loch
010_Obelisk}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af7
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
In this video, I present the new Protoss structure the }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Obelisk}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
The Obelisk is a new }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\dbch\af6\loch
defensive structure}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
 for the Protoss.\line It }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\dbch\af6\loch
slows the movement and attack speed}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
 of all nearby }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\dbch\af6\loch
enemy ground units}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
.\line In addition, the Obelisk has a }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\dbch\af6\loch
special shield}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
 that reduces all incoming damage }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\dbch\af6\loch
below 70 to just 1}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Because of this, each race needs }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\dbch\af6\loch
specific units}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
 to quickly destroy an Obelisk.\line Alternatively, players can try to destroy the Pylons or Warp Prism that project the Psionic Matrix, which powers the Obelisk.\line Without Psionic Matrix, }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\dbch\af6\loch
neither the slowing effect nor the special shield}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
 will function. This makes Pylons even more valuable targets, but also harder to destroy when surrounded by Obelisks.\line \line Rushes with ground units become much easier to defend against, allowing Protoss to }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\dbch\af6\loch
hold their ground even on completely open maps}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af7\loch
020_Photon Cannon}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af7
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
In this video, I present the changes made to the Photon Cannon.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
In the current version of StarCraft 2, defensive structures, including Photon Cannons, are generally too weak. Especially in team games, static defenses need to be strong enough to buy time until teammates can arrive to help. This is essential for team maps where players don\u8217\'92t start close to each other. However, even in 1v1 matches, defensive structures should remain a meaningful challenge for attacking players throughout the entire game, at least until they have units designed to counter static defenses.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
That\u8217\'92s why,}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 in }{\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\b0\loch
sc2YouWant}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
def}{\loch
ensive structures deal more damage and have increased health, shields, and range. The main design challenge is ensuring that they aren\u8217\'92t too powerful during early rushes. To balance this, defensive structures take longer to build, town halls with stored workers are armed with a weapon that has a range of 8, and workers deal significantly more damage to structures. }
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
These changes make a wider variety of maps viable, both in 1v1 and team games, and give players earlier and more accessible options to defend against rushes using static defenses.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af7\loch
030_Gateway Warpgate}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af7
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
In this video, I present the changes to the Gateway.\line After researching the Warp Gate upgrade, Gateways automatically transform into Warp Gates, which allow you to produce units within a few seconds anywhere covered by a Psionic Matrix. The Warp Gate then has a cooldown period that varies depending on the unit produced. This cooldown is shorter than the unit\u8217\'92s regular build time in a Gateway. This means that Warp Gates can produce units faster and also save travel time, since you can freely choose the warp-in location within the Psionic Matrix. As a result, Gateways become obsolete after upgrading to Warp Gates, and the Warp Gate upgrade becomes a mandatory choice regardless of the strategy you play. The short time it takes to warp in a unit also gives opponents very little opportunity to interrupt the warp-in. }
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
To add a more interesting strategic decision to the game, each warp-in now costs 25 minerals. This means you should gain some benefit from using a warp-in to make it worthwhile, for example, by dealing damage to your opponent, defending your buildings or workers more effectively, or creating an army faster to execute specific timing attacks. If none of these apply, it\u8217\'92s more cost-efficient to produce units in a Gateway instead.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
In addition, the warp-in duration has been slightly increased to give opponents a better chance to react. To make switching between Gateway and Warp Gate a more appealing option, the transformation time has been shortened. After researching the Warp Gate upgrade, Gateways no longer automatically transform into Warp Gates. In addition, the cooldown time for the Stalker has been slightly increased, while the cooldowns for all other Warp Gate units have been slightly decreased.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
With these changes, Gateways and Warp Gates now support different strategies, and Warp Gates are not always the better choice. Opponents can also react more effectively to warp-ins, which means Protoss players have to use them more carefully.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af7\loch
040_Zealot}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af7
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
In this video, I present the changes to the Zealot.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
The Zealot\u8217\'92s }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Charge}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 ability is designed to be easy to use, which is why it activates automatically whenever enemies are nearby. Because of this, it only works when the Zealot can actually attack enemy units, and not when retreating or performing other tactical maneuvers.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
To make Charge useful in more situations, it has been changed to grant a large temporary speed boost. This allows Zealots to quickly reposition, move across the map faster, or retreat from dangerous situations depending on the circumstances. This makes attacking with Zealots more demanding, but it also creates many new tactical opportunities.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
As before, the Charge upgrade also provides a general movement speed bonus, giving players with lower micro skills a good reason to research it as well.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
In addition, all Protoss units and structures now have more }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
shields}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 than }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
health}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
. The cost and research time of the armor upgrades from the Forge have been adjusted accordingly. Zealots in particular have received an additional increase to their shields, since the defensive options against them have improved for all races.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
The Zealot now offers new possibilities for all players, with its potential scaling better with player micro skill.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af7\loch
050_Sentry}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af7
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
In this video, I present the changes made to the }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Sentry}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
We\u8217\'92ll start with the changes to Force Field. Force Fields that could previously only be destroyed by certain units automatically led to situations where players only needed to build a few specific units to deal with Sentries effectively.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
Therefore, Force Fields are now }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
destructible}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 and have }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
high passive shield regeneration}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
ensuring that only a critical number of units is needed to destroy them instead of a specific unit. It\u8217\'92s perfectly fine that large armies can destroy Force Fields quickly, since such a cheap unit and ability shouldn\u8217\'92t be able to block entire armies worth thousands of minerals and vespen gas. However, Force Fields still have value even against large armies, because for a short time they absorb damage that would otherwise hit your actual units. The smaller the enemy army, the longer it takes to bring down the Force Fields, and the more value they provide. This means that Force Fields remain just as effective as before against }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
run-bys}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 and }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
small armies}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
. As a result, Force Fields still serve an important purpose but now allow for many more ways to be countered, which increases the variety of viable unit compositions.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
To compensate for the Force Field nerf, Guardian Shield has been slightly strengthened to make Sentries with an active Guardian Shield a more threatening unit, one that, like Templars, opponents will want to focus down. As a result, Guardian Shield now reduces incoming damage by 3 instead of 2 per attack. This makes it more effective against units like }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Marines}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 or }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Hydralisks}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
encouraging opponents to mix in other units that counter Sentries with Guardian Shield more effectively.\line \line Moving on to Hallucinations. Sentry Hallucinations have too little variation, which leads players to mainly use fast flying units like the Phoenix for scouting, or high-HP units to soak up damage. Other Hallucinations usually aren\u8217\'92t worth using. }
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
Now, Hallucinations last longer and deal }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
25% of the original unit\u8217\'92s damage}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
so different damage types and attributes matter more, and attacking Hallucinations can be more easily mistaken for real units. To prevent Hallucinations from being by far the best scouting option or generally too strong at the beginning of the game, they now have to be researched at the Twilight Council, and their vision range has been reduced to 5. Reducing their vision range also makes it worthwhile to mix melee and ranged unit Hallucinations, since ranged units can only fully use their attack range if melee Hallucinations reveal nearby targets. Additionally, the }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
number of Hallucinations}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
 created now varies depending on the unit, adding another factor that differentiates them.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Moreover, the Sentry\u8217\'92s attack damage has been increased, especially against light units and structures. Its starting energy has also been increased so that Guardian Shield can be used immediately, just like Force Field, while offering a different tactical purpose. While Force Field is stronger against melee units such as Zerglings, Firebats, or Zealots, Guardian Shield is more effective against ranged units with a high attack rate, like Hydralisks, Marines, or Sentries and Hallucinations have additional, distinct use cases depending on the hallucinated unit. }{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\loch
\line \line All in all, the strengths of the abilities have been redistributed through these changes, making all abilities roughly equally useful. With the additional damage, the Sentry becomes more of a glass cannon, but now has more options to protect itself through the use of its abilities.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af7\loch
060_Stalker}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af7
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
In this video, I present the changes made to the }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Stalker}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
The Stalker is a fast unit that can take a fair amount of damage while also dealing solid damage itself. There\u8217\'92s really nothing to criticize about the Stalker, even its ability, }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Blink}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
is one of the most iconic and best-designed abilities in }{\rtlch\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i\b0\dbch\af6\loch
StarCraft II}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
. It offers great potential for players to get more value out of the unit as their micro skills improve, opening up new tactical and strategic possibilities.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
To give the Stalker even more tactical and strategic flexibility, it now has }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
two Blink charges}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
each with a }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
14-second cooldown}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
 instead of 7 seconds. This ensures that, overall, the Stalker cannot Blink more frequently than before. Without the increased cooldown, it would effectively be able to Blink every 3.5 seconds instead of every 7 seconds. With this change, it can either Blink once every 7 seconds as before, or twice every 14 seconds. This also helps further distinguish Blink from the Dark Templar\u8217\'92s }{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Shadow Step}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
 ability, which, unlike the Stalker\u8217\'92s, is a single-use Blink that, combined with the Dark Templar\u8217\'92s invisibility, already provides sufficient escape or engagement potential.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
The updated Blink mechanic allows Stalkers to snipe enemy units more effectively while reducing losses, since they can now Blink out of danger earlier. }{\dbch\af6\loch
It also makes it easier to chase down certain targets, though success still depends on reading the situation correctly and having good timing.}{\rtlch\ab0 \ltrch\loch\b0\dbch\af6\loch
 Using both Blinks too quickly can leave a Stalker without an escape option for a while, which makes it a lot riskier.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af7\loch
070_Adept}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af7
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052{\dbch\af6\loch
In this video, I present the changes to the Adept. \line \line The Adept was introduced as an early-game harassment and scouting option that also serves as a threat to light units such as Zerglings. \line \line To strengthen the Adept in this role and give it more versatility, its shields now regenerate significantly faster outside of combat. In addition, its Shade can now reveal burrowed and cloacked units, has a shorter cooldown, and the Adept no longer automatically teleports to the Shade after a certain amount of time, but can instead be manually teleported to the Shade at any time through a new button. This makes harassment with the Adept more micro-intensive but provides more options, while pure scouting with the Shade has become less micro-intensive. Due to the reduced cooldown, the Adept can retreat from danger more quickly, and thanks to the faster shield regeneration, it can re-engage in battle sooner. Furthermore, the Adept\u8217\'92s overall damage has been increased to make it less of a niche unit and more effective against all ground units and structures. \line }
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\dbch\af6\loch
Overall, the effectiveness of Adept harassment now relies more on micro skill, while both scouting and combat with the Adept have generally improved.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af7\loch
080_High Templar}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af7
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
In this video, I\u8217\'92ll be presenting the changes made to the }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
High Templar}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Let\u8217\'92s start with the }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Feedback}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
 ability. \line Because most units and structures now have higher health and shield values, the damage Feedback deals per energy point has also been increased. }
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
This means Feedback remains roughly as strong as before and might even be seen more often now, since more units have energy than before.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Now let\u8217\'92s move on to }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Psi Storm}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
.\line In }{\rtlch\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
StarCraft: Brood War}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Psi Storm dealt less overall damage because of the weaker movement AI and the unit grouping limit, meaning fewer units were hit at once. As a result, the area of effect could be larger without becoming overpowered. In StarCraft II, however, the improved movement AI and the unlimited control group size caused more units to be hit by a storm. Because of this, the radius was reduced in the beta of }{\rtlch\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Wings of Liberty}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
 from 2 to 1.5. But the real issue, both then and now, wasn\u8217\'92t Psi Storm itself, but rather the changed movement AI. And I say \u8220\'93changed,\u8221\'94 not \u8220\'93improved,\u8221\'94 because it also introduced unnecessary drawbacks. For example, units now automatically clump together, which actually }{\rtlch\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
reduces}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
 player control instead of enhancing it.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
That\u8217\'92s why, ever since the early development of }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
sc2YouWant}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
I\u8217\'92ve modified Psi Storm so that it deals }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
less damage per second}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
covers a }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
larger area}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
and }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
lasts longer}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
.\line This turns Psi Storm into a great zoning tool long before the latest patches, rather than just being a burst-damage ability. It\u8217\'92s better for opponents because it causes fewer game-ending moments and allows more comeback potential, and it\u8217\'92s also better for the caster, since the larger area and zoning effect make it more reliable and rewarding even with imperfect placement.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Aside from ability changes, the }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Templar can now attack air units}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
 and no longer fires a visible projectile. Instead, the attack resembles the one seen in the }{\rtlch\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Legacy of the Void}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
 cinematic trailer. It strikes a single target with a lightning attack that deals damage multiple times over a short duration.\line This not only looks cooler in-game and increases immersion, but it also adds gameplay depth: the attack deals extra damage against }{\rtlch\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
armored}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
 units and has a range of }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
7}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
giving the High Templar more utility even without Psi Storm.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Overall, these changes make High Templar more versatile. Feedback now has a slightly broader range of applications, and Psi Storm no longer almost completely defines the unit\u8217\'92s role, though it remains a powerful spell. The Templar\u8217\'92s strengths and weaknesses are now more balanced, opening up new strategies and unit combinations.}
