\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
In this video, I present the changes to the Dark Templar.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1\widctlpar\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Aside from the standard changes that most units have received, nothing has changed for the Dark Templar. The Dark Templar did not receive a double-blink like the Stalker, because its invisibility already gives it frequent opportunities to get to its targets or escape danger. That is also the core ability that defines the Dark Templar, and the simple Blink, or in this case,\~Shadow Step\~, is more than enough to give it a micro-dependent ability, allowing players to better showcase their skill when engaging, disengaging, or overcoming obstacles.}
