\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
In this video, I present the changes to the Observer.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
The Observer is no longer revealed while in Surveillance Mode. Its vision and detection range have been reduced, now matching those of the Overseer. Since the Raven doesn\u8217\'92t have a stationary mode that grants extended vision and detection range, it always has the increased vision and detection range of the Observer and Overseer in their stationary modes. Because of the overall reduction in vision and detection range, revealing the Observer is no longer necessary.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af7\loch
120_Immortal}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af7
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
In this video, I showcase the changes made to the Immortal.\line Previously, the Immortal lost its Hardened Shield because it was simply too powerful against Terran mech, especially Siege Tanks. While countering Siege Tanks has always been the Immortal\u8217\'92s intended role, Hardened Shield did so }{\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i\b0\loch
too}{\loch
 effectively. At the same time, the Immortal became too easily countered by units with low damage but very high attack speed, such as Zerglings or Marines. The current Barrier only lasts a few seconds, which makes it insufficiently impactful against heavily fortified defenses.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
To address this, the Barrier now blocks significantly more damage and lasts much longer, but it also has a noticeably longer cooldown before it can activate again. A new upgrade in the Robotics Bay can further extend its active duration, reducing the time it remains inactive. For better immersion, the visual appearance of the Barrier has also been updated to resemble the iconic shield from early concept art, fully enveloping the Immortal.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
These Barrier changes encourage opponents to try to trigger it early, forcing it to expire before Immortals reach their defensive lines. Active scouting and brief hit-and-run engagements become more important to keep fortified positions secure over time. I see this as a fresh form of base defense, one that urges even heavily turtling players to move out of their bases occasionally in order to preserve them. At the same time, the improved Barrier gives attackers a temporary window to break through defenses if the opponent doesn\u8217\'92t respond quickly enough. And beyond that, the stronger Barrier also gives Immortals more opportunities to retreat or be reinforced by supporting units.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af7\loch
130_Disruptor}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af7
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
In this video, I\u8217\'92m presenting the changes to the Disruptor.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Right now, the Disruptor can destroy far too many units with a single Purification Nova, and its cooldown is also too long, which leaves the Disruptor unable to deal damage and completely vulnerable afterward. This creates frustration on both sides: one player often loses a large number of units because of a small micro mistake or a brief moment of inattention, while the other player is very likely to lose their Disruptor. The relatively short lifetime and range of the Purification Nova make these situations even more likely to happen.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
A better design can reduce the chances of these extreme outcomes for both players. }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
With the new version in the SC}{\rtlch\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
2YouWant}{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
 mod,}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
 the Purification Nova deals high damage in a much smaller area and lower damage in the remaining area. At the same time, the cooldown is significantly reduced, and the Nova\u8217\'92s lifetime, and therefore its effective range, is increased. }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
This gives the defending player more time to react and reduces the number of units lost due to mis-micro or a brief lapse in attention. On the other side, the Purification Nova can be used from a safer distance, allowing for better positioning and more room for precise timing. However, the increased lifetime of the Purification Nova also gives the opponent more time to respond.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Overall, the Disruptor can be used with less risk, but also requires multiple well-placed shots to deal massive damage, creating more room for mistakes, learning moments, and comebacks on both sides.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af7\loch
140_Colossus}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af7
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
In this video, I present the changes made to the Colossus.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
The Colossus\u8217\'92 attack is a horizontal line that naturally matches the formation of enemy units, which automatically line up next to each other when attacking. This attack design was originally introduced with the argument that it should reward micro-management and proper positioning. Unfortunately, positioning is usually automatically correct, and maps as well as classic unit compositions severely limit the room for creative positioning. As a result, it almost never happens that Colossi approach from a different direction than the main army. Since Colossi cannot defend themselves against air units, yet can be attacked by pure anti-air units, they are far too vulnerable to move around on their own. In practice, the idea of flexible positioning does not fit the reality of gameplay. It feels more like a punishment when a Colossus is not standing directly inside the main army to deal optimal damage, for example, when a newly built Colossus reinforces from a different angle.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
Even their cliff-walking ability is hardly usable, because, again, they are too vulnerable when alone, especially against air units, and there are too few units like Stalkers that can follow them over cliffs by using Blink. I don\u8217\'92t know for sure, but I could imagine that Blizzard\u8217\'92s original idea was that the Colossus should function on many maps like a combination of Shuttle and Reaver from StarCraft: Brood War, except that the Colossus cannot move over water and thus has more limitations, giving players a reason to sometimes still use a Warp Prism for transportation. }
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
To return to its weapon, Dustin Browder said in 2009 that :}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\fi0\li567\lin567\ri567\rin567\sb0\sa283{\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\loch\cf0\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052
\u8220\'93}{\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\loch\cf0\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\loch
The original attack is not coming back. The old beam was just \u8216\'91more damage.\u8217\'92 Simple, but not fun. The current Colossus weapon encourages micro since it really matters who you shoot and the angle you shoot them from. Fortunately since the Colossus can step up and down cliffs and over friendly units he can move to the optimal position if you are fast enough.\u8221\'94}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
For me, this falls into a similiar category as: }{\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i\b0\loch
\u8220\'93Do you guys not have phones?\u8221\'94}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
Do you often see players having fun with Colossus positioning? Do you see many interesting positional plays against deathballs that show a clear difference between beginners and professional players? I simply don\u8217\'92t. Maybe most players just aren\u8217\'92t fast enough.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
That is why the Colossus weapon is now again a continuous single-target attack, similar to a Sentry beam, but with automatic target locking and area-of-effect damage that also works against air units. The target lock ensures that the weapon has extended range as long as the Colossus continues attacking the same enemy unit. If the target or Colossus moves outside that extended range, the continuous beam breaks. This makes the Colossus flexible enough to operate alone on the map and hold its own against any unit type, although there are still dedicated counters that can take it down efficiently.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
Additionally, the new weapon deals damage while moving, which is useful both when chasing and when retreating, and it makes micro with the Colossus genuinely enjoyable. You try to activate the attack, but immediately keep moving so the Colossus stays out of range of enemy units. The new danger posed by the Colossus also makes it an interesting harassment unit. Opponents need to hunt it down and can counter the attack effectively if they maintain proper spacing between units to avoid the splash damage.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
Overall, this creates more interesting micro on both sides and allows for more diverse unit compositions.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af7\loch
150_Phoenix}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af7
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s19\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
In this video, I present the changes made to the Phoenix.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
The Phoenix originally used }{\rtlch\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Graviton Beam}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
 to lift single units, limited by its energy, which theoretically made sense against expensive targets. But those targets are usually }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
not}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
 light units\u8230\'85 while the Phoenix deals }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
bonus damage to light}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
.\line On top of that, Graviton Beam has short range, and the Phoenix can\u8217\'92t move or attack while channeling it. So the ability ended up being useful only in very specific cases.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
We mostly saw Phoenixes harassing workers, where the bonus vs. light actually matters. But once the Oracle arrived with }{\rtlch\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Pulsar Beam}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
 as a far stronger worker-harass tool, the Phoenix quickly lost that role and Graviton Beam became even rarer.\line These days, the Phoenix mostly appears as a counter to Mutalisks, making it a very niche unit overall.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
To give the Phoenix more meaningful use cases, it can now attack both }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
ground and air}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
deals increased damage vs. light units, and is once again a solid harassment option. To avoid making it too strong, its damage vs. non-light targets, movement speed, and acceleration have been toned down.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Graviton Beam has been removed entirely, since the Phoenix no longer needs it to fight ground units, including massive ones. And since we already have Stasis Ward as a crowd-control option, one that works on more unit types and can be countered by destroying the Ward or reacting to its activation delay, a single-target disable like Graviton Beam, which stops the Phoenix from moving and can only be ended by killing the Phoenix itself, simply wasn\u8217\'92t needed anymore.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Air dominance against Mutalisks now depends more on }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
active micro}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
: the Phoenix has slower acceleration and must stay in motion to keep its speed advantage. It\u8217\'92s no longer an automatic hard counter, only when properly controlled.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
Meanwhile, the Oracle now fills a different role: Pulsar Beam is gone, replaced by an anti-air weapon with bonus damage vs. armored }{\dbch\af6\loch
and an activatable shield that reduces small hits below 15 damage to 1. }{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
This makes the Oracle strong against armored air or for hunting Overlords, without being shut down too easily by Marines or Hydras.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\dbch\af6\loch
So overall, the Phoenix is weaker in some ways after losing Graviton Beam, but it has become a more general counter to light units, both on the ground and in the air, and a less limited harassment unit that truly rewards micro-skill.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af7\loch
160_Void Ray}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af7
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
In this video, I will be presenting the changes to the Void Ray.\line \line Traditionally, the Void Ray has been designed as an anti-armored unit that can deal with both ground and air targets. }{\loch
Its overall design has always made it difficult to keep it from becoming either too strong in general or too limited in its use cases. }
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
To give it a wider range of applications, the Void Ray now deals a lot more bonus damage against }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
massive units}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
 and }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
structures}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
 instead of armored units. Its ability, }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Prismatic Alignment}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
, now }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
triples all of its damage}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
 rather than only increasing its damage against armored targets. To ensure solid counterplay still exists, its attack range has been slightly reduced, and it now moves significantly slower while Prismatic Alignment is active. The duration of the ability has been increased, but so has the cooldown.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
Because units generally move a bit slower in }{\rtlch\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\loch
sc2YouWant}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
, the }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
Flux Vanes}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
 upgrade now provides a much more noticeable movement-speed boost. This allows the Void Ray to dive into enemy bases quickly, apply pressure, and destroy key structures at high speed. Combined with the higher life and shield values in }{\rtlch\ai\ab0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\loch
sc2YouWant}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
, the Void Ray also has a better chance of escaping dangerous situations. Since massive units are generally slow and structures are immobile, the reduced range and speed matter much less in those fights, while still opening up more counterplay options for other units.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
Overall, these changes aim to ensure that the Void Ray is neither too powerful nor too limited in its use cases. In large-scale battles, activating Prismatic Alignment can result in extremely dangerous burst damage against all targets, forcing opponents to either }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
relocate the fight}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
 or quickly }{\rtlch\ai0\ab \ltrch\loch\cs16\rtlch\ai \ltrch\loch\i\i0\b0\loch
focus-fire the Void Rays}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
. Relocating is often a viable response, since the Void Ray becomes very slow while Prismatic Alignment is active. This also means you need to carefully choose how many Void Rays will use Prismatic Alignment, and how you position them beforehand.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af7\loch
170_Oracle}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af7
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
In this video, I\u8217\'92ll be showcasing the changes to the Oracle.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
The Oracle now fully takes over the harassment role previously filled by the Phoenix\u8217\'92s Graviton Beam. Pulsar Beam allows the Oracle to kill more workers with the same amount of energy, making it more effective at economic harassment and also better at defending against Zergling run-bys. This gives the Oracle a stronger defensive purpose as well. In addition, Stasis Ward can disable large groups of units for a significant amount of time, while Revelation provides safe and reliable scouting. As a result, there are now only a few situations where a Phoenix is clearly the better choice, for example when facing Mutalisks.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
Because the Phoenix\u8217\'92s role has shifted into a general counter to light units, both air and ground, the Oracle\u8217\'92s role has been redesigned as well. It now comes with a built-in weapon that can only target air units but deals high bonus damage to armored targets. Pulsar Beam has been removed, since that niche is now covered by the Phoenix. The Oracle has also gained a new ability: }{\rtlch\ai0 \ltrch\loch\cs15\rtlch\ab \ltrch\loch\b\i0\b0\loch
Absorption Shield}{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
. When activated, it continuously drains energy but reduces all incoming damage below 15 to only 1. This gives the Oracle greater durability against Marines and Hydralisks and forces opponents to invest in more appropriate counters. As a result, Oracles have become extremely effective at sniping Overlords and present a new type of threat that doesn\u8217\'92t revolve around killing workers.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
However, workers and other ground units can still be trapped in a quickly deployable Stasis Ward. This allows the Oracle to harass and delay the opponent without permanently removing units, buying time or making it easier to pick off Overlords and other air units. Stasis Ward has also been adjusted so that it can be placed faster and lasts much longer. }{\loch
To make it easier to counter, the delay between triggering the trap and the actual Stasis has been slightly increased, and the duration of the Stasis effect has been slightly reduced.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
These changes also make Stasis Ward more viable for defensive play, since it no longer has to be constantly replaced. Offensively, it can now be used with less risk of losing the Oracle, and enemy units have a bit more time to avoid being caught.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
Now let\u8217\'92s talk about Revelation. Previously, Revelation covered too large an area and was available too often. To encourage more thoughtful use, its energy cost has been increased and its radius reduced.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\rtlch\ai0\ab0 \ltrch\loch\i0\b0\loch
Overall, the redesigned Oracle opens up new unit compositions and strategies. It is a more reliable and balanced tool that feels fairer for both players, since its abilities are no longer based on an \u8220\'93all-or-nothing\u8221\'94 design philosophy.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af7\loch
180_Tempest}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af7
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
In this video, I\u8217\'92m presenting the changes made to the Tempest.\line The Tempest was originally designed as a siege unit, effective against both ground and air targets. It has lost its role as a weapon against large groups of flying light units, such as Mutalisks, because Blizzard believes that mass Mutas should be countered through micro to make battles more exciting and create more player interaction. In principle, that\u8217\'92s a good idea, but we shouldn\u8217\'92t forget that you also need an effective counter against large numbers of units, so you can respond through a tactical decision in a reasonable amount of time instead of losing instantly. Most players are not familiar with the meta and won\u8217\'92t preemptively build enough Phoenixes, for example. Most of them are surprised by Mutas and cannot produce sufficient Phoenixes quickly enough. Additionally, Terran has several units, such as the Thor and Liberator, that can counter many Mutalisks very well. This implies that even if Blizzard\u8217\'92s justification is reasonable, their actions lack consistency. Being able to counter large masses with a few units is an essential requirement for comebacks, and those are exactly what we, as players and viewers, want to see more of.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
Because of this, the Tempest\u8217\'92s air attack now deals area-of-effect damage, bonus damage against light, and has slightly reduced range. Against ground targets, the Tempest retains its role as a siege unit, since there are already plenty of counters available against masses of ground units. The Tectonic Destabilizers upgrade has been removed, its bonus damage against structures has been increased by default, and its range has been increased slightly. This allows it to break defensive positions effectively even in small numbers.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
We should not forget that in sc2YouWant, units no longer automatically clump, there is a button to quickly spread units across a larger area, and with a single click in the middle of your army, you can make units clump together again. This allows area damage to be countered more effectively in general. It creates micro potential and player interaction. You now have to react to the opponent\u8217\'92s army formation, which you didn\u8217\'92t need to do before, because there was only a single formation back then. What happened automatically in StarCraft: Brood War, units keeping more distance, is now a deliberate decision the player can make in sc2YouWant. This means you can still fight with clumped armies like before, but since AoE damage has been generally strengthened, you will be less successful doing so in more situations.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
As a result, Protoss have a faster answer to large groups of Mutalisks and big air armies in general, while the Tempest can still be used very effectively as a siege unit, especially against structures.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af7\loch
190_Arbiter}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af7
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
In this video, I\u8217\'92ll explain why the Mothership has been removed from the game and why it has been replaced by the Arbiter.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
The Mothership is a unit that you can only build once, which automatically means it has to be stronger than other units, since its power cannot come from mass production like it does for all other units. Unfortunately, this also leads to tactical and strategic limitations, because you can\u8217\'92t use its abilities in multiple locations or multiple times across different army groups. Due to its strength, the Mothership usually becomes a priority target, as it always represents the highest threat on the battlefield. Unfortunately, this causes the entire game to revolve around this single unit, which actually reduces overall diversity. Additionally, I simply prefer the Arbiter model over the Mothership model, which is a very subjective reason, but not the only one. The Arbiter\u8217\'92s smaller model improves visibility on the battlefield.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
For these reasons, and because it wouldn\u8217\'92t feel appropriate to have multiple Motherships, and because its large model obscures too many units and reduces visual clarity, it has been replaced by the Arbiter. The Arbiter can be built multiple times, deals bonus damage to armored units and structures, and its abilities cost energy instead of having cooldowns. This makes the Arbiter useful in more situations and gives it more counters.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
Now let\u8217\'92s take a look at its abilities. Instead of having a passive cloaking effect, the Arbiter, just like the Mothership, has Cloaking Field, which makes the Arbiter and all nearby friendly units invisible for a limited duration. The fact that the Arbiter itself also becomes invisible makes it harder to counter, but it also enables ambushes that wouldn\u8217\'92t be possible with a visible Arbiter. As a result, detection and good scouting become increasingly important. Draining the Arbiter\u8217\'92s energy early and using area-of-effect damage that works on cloaked units become important tools against it.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
The next ability is Time Warp, which now increases the movement and attack speed of all units inside the field instead of slowing them. This change was made because Protoss already have plenty of abilities that restrict enemy movement, such as the Obelisk slow, Force Field, and Stasis Ward. This version of Time Warp is also more counterable, because there are more ways to push units out of it than there are ways to force units into it. As a result, players are incentivized to push enemy units out and move their own units in to benefit. This increases player interaction, can lead to more varied outcomes in matches, and scales well with player skill when contesting specific areas.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
The final ability is Transference, which replaces Mass Recall. Transference teleports all nearby friendly units into a Psionic Matrix. This allows units to not only escape dangerous situations, but also, with the help of a Warp Prism, to be teleported behind enemy lines. Additionally, units can be teleported not just to a Nexus, but anywhere a Psionic Matrix exists. This makes the ability significantly more flexible and opens up more tactical and strategic possibilities.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
Overall, the Arbiter is a support unit that improves mobility and enhances friendly units. These new options enable fresh tactical responses and strategic depth.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\pagebb\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\cf1\fs32\b\f4\dbch\af7\loch
200_Carrier}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sb0\sa240{\rtlch\af7\afs24 \ltrch\loch\cf1\dbch\af7
\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f\u9472\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
In this video, I present the changes made to the Carrier.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
Currently, a Carrier\u8217\'92s Interceptors deal the same amount of damage against all unit types, and Carriers become very difficult to counter in large numbers. Additionally, a Carrier starts with only 4 out of 8 Interceptors, meaning it isn\u8217\'92t at full strength immediately after being built. This can be especially punishing in defensive situations where every unit counts, making Carriers less effective as comeback units despite their high cost.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1{\loch
To give the Carrier clearer strengths and weaknesses, the Interceptors\u8217\'92 base damage has been reduced but increased against armored units. To ensure the Carrier is immediately combat-ready, it now starts with 8 out of 8 Interceptors, which can also operate farther away from the Carrier, improving its potential to turn games around. Interceptors now build faster, but they also cost more minerals. As a result, the Carrier becomes a strong siege unit, while being more effectively countered by non-armored units. Losing large numbers of Interceptors becomes costly, making it more worthwhile to focus fire on them if the Carrier itself is out of range.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af5\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\loch
Overall, Interceptors are now easier to counter and destroying them provides a greater reward because they are more expensive. At the same time, the Carrier is fully effective right away, can reposition more safely after launching its Interceptors, and can replenish them more quickly. This makes the Carrier a strong siege option with clearer counterplay.}
